724957f-a.text:
2nd Street, west side, north from 27th to 26th Avencee, showing the lumber yard of the Tisdale Lumber Company (1928 Maap). Second Street, here, was formerly knoam as Munson Street.
P. L. Sperr  March 11, 1931

724954f-b.text:
2nd Street, west side, north of 26th Avenue, on the East River, showing the Astoria Light and what Mr. Sperr calls the Board of Education Building. Here was located Fort Stevens and United States Government Works. In 1873 the Eagle Oil Works
occupied the site.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: June, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 2,3: March, 1931
